ENTRY            F1072   20251230   20260311   20260311       F107
SUBENT        F1072001   20251230   20260311   20260311       F107
BIB                 11         38
TITLE      1.7 MeV anomaly in the 12C(p,p)12C reaction
AUTHOR     (J.C.Armstrong,M.J.Baggett,W.R.Harris,V.A.Latorre)
INSTITUTE  (1USAMRY)
REFERENCE  (J,PR,144,823,1966)
           #doi:10.1103/PhysRev.144.823
FACILITY   (VDG,1USAMRY) 3 MV Van de Graaff accelerator.
INC-SPECT  The energy spread within the beam is typically
           <=0.3 keV.
DETECTOR   (MAGSP) Scattered protons were analyzed with a
           180 degr. double-focusing magnetic spectrometer having
           a mean radius of curvature of 50.8 cm for the analyzed
           particles. The maximum spectrometer solid angle is
           0.025 sr, the magnification is unity, and the best
           resolution is dp/p=9*10**(-4). The spectrometer is
           coupled to the scattering chamber through a sliding
           seal of 0.32 mm beryllium copper foil. This arrangement
           permits the spectrometer to be rotated under vacuum
           from a scattering angle of 30 degr. on one side of the
           beam to 130 degr. on the other side.
           (SOLST) Scattered protons were deflected through a slip
           system located in the focal plane of the spectrometer
           and were detected with a large area solid state
           detector.
SAMPLE     Self-supporting carbon targets were prepared both by
           deposition onto a glass plate from a carbon arc and by
           cracking methyl iodide onto a thin nickel foil. In both
           cases the carbon film was floated from its backing onto
           a water surface. After reducing the surface tension of
           the water by adding a small amount of detergent, the
           foils could be easily lifted from the water onto thin
           aluminum frames.
METHOD     (BCINT)
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-1) The relative cross sections are more accurately
           determined, the errors being typically only about 3%.
HISTORY    (20100624C)
           (20251229U) SD: Small corrections in all Subents.
           Subents 002-007 were merged; 009 and 010 were merged.
           ERR-SYS -> ERR-T; ERR-S -> ERR-1.
ENDBIB              38
COMMON               1          3
ERR-1
PER-CENT
         3.
ENDCOMMON            3
ENDSUBENT           45
SUBENT        F1072002   20251230   20260311   20260311       F107
BIB                  4          4
REACTION   (6-C-12(P,EL)6-C-12,,DA)
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-T) Total uncertainty
STATUS     (CURVE,,J.C.Armstrong+,J,PR,144,823,1966) Fig.1(a)
HISTORY    (20251230U) SD: BIB updated. DATA-ERR -> ERR-T.
ENDBIB               4
COMMON               1          3
EN-ERR-DIG
MEV
     0.0004
ENDCOMMON            3
